01:23.294 --> 01:25.993
♪ ♪

01:46.701 --> 01:47.803
Nice.

01:47.805 --> 01:48.930
Nice hands, man.

01:48.932 --> 01:49.936
Awesome hands.

01:49.938 --> 01:51.429
Let's see your arm.

01:53.270 --> 01:55.899
Whoa, whoa.

01:56.836 --> 01:57.937
Sorry.

01:57.939 --> 01:59.733
Don't worry about
it-- come here.

02:02.635 --> 02:03.600
See the laces?

02:03.602 --> 02:06.261
The laces are there
for a reason, right?

02:06.263 --> 02:07.299
Yeah.

02:07.301 --> 02:08.298
Use them.

02:08.300 --> 02:09.991
Show me.

02:09.994 --> 02:13.764
Find the grooves,
find the grooves.

02:13.766 --> 02:14.699
Keep this loose.

02:14.701 --> 02:16.100
Okay.
All right?

02:16.102 --> 02:18.194
Tight.

02:20.370 --> 02:22.462
Let it roll through.

02:22.464 --> 02:23.900
That's right.

02:23.902 --> 02:24.867
That's right, nice.

02:24.869 --> 02:25.834
You feel that?

02:25.836 --> 02:27.328
Yeah.

02:27.330 --> 02:29.000
Right?

02:30.665 --> 02:32.304
Joe.

02:32.306 --> 02:34.198
Steve, where's Danny?

02:36.010 --> 02:37.672
He's at Grace's school
for career day. Why?

02:37.674 --> 02:39.376
Get him out of there now.

02:39.378 --> 02:40.943
Why? What's going on?

02:40.945 --> 02:43.105
There's no time to explain--
just get him out of there.

02:44.110 --> 02:45.179
We got to go.

02:45.181 --> 02:47.147
Come on.

02:47.149 --> 02:51.512
So like, uh, like I said,
our job is to uphold the laws

02:51.514 --> 02:52.815
of this great country.

02:52.817 --> 02:54.982
Without policemen,
without policewomen,

02:54.984 --> 02:56.046
uh, there'd
be no order.

02:56.048 --> 02:57.517
And order is, um...

02:57.519 --> 03:00.515
it's the backbone
to any civilized society.

03:00.517 --> 03:03.721
And, yes, I like doughnuts
very much.

03:05.185 --> 03:06.519
If anybody has
any questions,

03:06.521 --> 03:08.191
uh, please, you
can ask them now.

03:08.193 --> 03:09.191
Yes.

03:09.193 --> 03:11.326
What's it like
cutting up dead people?

03:11.328 --> 03:12.789
I don't do that.

03:12.791 --> 03:14.291
I was asking him.

03:14.293 --> 03:16.427
Ah.

03:16.429 --> 03:18.361
The vivisection of a
once-living organism

03:18.363 --> 03:21.263
as a scientific necessity
can be quite rewarding

03:21.265 --> 03:22.759
if it yields
forensic results.

03:22.761 --> 03:24.231
Is it yucky?

03:24.233 --> 03:25.328
Quite the opposite.

03:25.330 --> 03:26.400
Thank you for asking.

03:26.402 --> 03:28.769
Okay, anybody else?

03:28.771 --> 03:29.972
Who else?

03:29.974 --> 03:31.444
Yes.

03:31.446 --> 03:34.612
You ever find anything weird
in the poop chute?

03:34.614 --> 03:36.947
Settle down.

03:36.949 --> 03:38.650
Young man,

03:38.652 --> 03:40.348
if you're referring to the anus
or the descending colon,

03:40.350 --> 03:41.756
then the answer is yes.

03:41.758 --> 03:43.125
Sometimes, foreign
objects can be found...

03:43.127 --> 03:44.389
Okay. Okay, Max,
that's good.

03:44.391 --> 03:46.524
Oh, thank you
for asking.

03:46.526 --> 03:50.394
Uh, anybody have any
police-related questions?

03:50.396 --> 03:51.826
Yeah.

03:51.828 --> 03:54.530
How old do you have to be
to join the police academy?

03:54.532 --> 03:56.034
Uh, well, that's not
a relevant question

03:56.036 --> 03:57.634
for someone who's gonna be
a marine biologist,

03:57.636 --> 03:59.571
- so we'll move on.
- Anybody else?

04:00.341 --> 04:02.277
Detective Daniel Williams?
Yeah.

04:02.279 --> 04:03.646
My name's Deputy Knox,
U.S. Marshals.

04:03.648 --> 04:05.415
Can you please place your hands
behind your back?

04:05.417 --> 04:06.912
Sure.

04:06.914 --> 04:08.680
What's this, uh,
what's this about?

04:08.682 --> 04:10.952
You're under arrest
for murder.

04:10.954 --> 04:13.023
You can't do this.
Sir, please step back.

04:13.025 --> 04:14.790
For murder?
What are you talking about?

04:14.792 --> 04:15.757
All right, let's go.

04:15.759 --> 04:16.757
Danno?

04:16.759 --> 04:17.923
All right, ho-ho-ho...

04:17.926 --> 04:18.923
Grace, it's all right.

04:18.925 --> 04:20.187
Listen, I'm gonna get this
figured out.

04:20.189 --> 04:21.290
I'll see you
at home, okay?

04:21.291 --> 04:22.290
Everything's fine.

04:22.292 --> 04:24.455
Hey, easy, easy.

04:27.158 --> 04:29.124
They give you any other details?

04:29.126 --> 04:30.764
No, Max said they just,
they walked right in,

04:30.766 --> 04:32.333
Th-they cuffed him,
and they hauled him away.

04:32.335 --> 04:33.566
Who's got Grace?

04:33.568 --> 04:35.473
Max is gonna take her
to Rachel's place.

04:35.475 --> 04:37.074
All right, I'm out the door.

04:37.076 --> 04:39.307
I'll meet you at the federal
detention center in ten.

04:42.582 --> 04:45.116
What's your rush,
Lieutenant?

04:45.118 --> 04:46.788
Coughlin.

04:46.790 --> 04:48.759
I don't know what you want,
but now is not the time.

04:48.761 --> 04:50.160
Unfortunately
for you, it is.

04:50.162 --> 04:51.128
Grab some hood.

04:51.130 --> 04:52.128
What?

04:52.130 --> 04:53.529
You're arresting
me? Right now?

04:53.531 --> 04:54.962
You got to be kidding.

04:54.964 --> 04:56.370
What's it for
this time?

04:56.372 --> 04:58.570
Bribery, tax evasion,
criminal misconduct,

04:58.572 --> 05:01.905
and my favorite,
conspiracy to commit murder.

05:01.907 --> 05:04.103
Told you
I'd catch you later.

